  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "The former involves pixel-level classification and segmentation, together called semantic segmentation.",
    "In contrast, while the latter incorporates a regression branch to estimate the four corners of the bounding box alongside the classification branch.",
    "Object detection using bounding boxes is faster than semantic segmentation and has been extensively utilized in real-time applications, such as sports broadcasting.",
    "For example You Only Live Once (YOLO) models for object detection and image segmentation (Redmon et al. 2016) only require one pass of a network to infer location.",
    "Furthermore, image masking can help YOLO reduce stationary noise (Yun and Park 2022) by excluding known pixels regions that do not contain relevant information during inference."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "For example You Only Live Once (YOLO) models for object detection and image segmentation (Redmon et al. 2016) only require one pass of a network to infer location.",
